Subject: [PATCH 1/3] feat(agentic): define grounded architect v2 contract
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The strict contract + deterministic truth the V2 grounded architect is validated against.

  - schemas.ts: CriterionGroundingV1 gains pageUrl/stateId/supportRationale; MissionGroundingV1 gains
    observationSetDigest (binds the map to the exact set that entered the architect); GroundingTier
    (action_replayed | action_observed | state_seen | inferred_only | ungrounded) — additional design/
    payout truth, never a replacement for verifiabilityClass. Four new validation codes.
  - mission-grounding.ts: validateMissionGrounding gains opts {expectedDigest, replayReproduced} and now
    also rejects: an observationSetDigest mismatch; duplicate / extra / negative / out-of-range criterion
    indices; a cited transition whose before/after state matches none of the cited facts; a claimed
    pageUrl/stateId that matches none of the cited facts (no unrelated-fact substitution). classifyGrounding
    Tier deterministically tiers a criterion — a `safe` reproduced transition → action_replayed; a safe
    observed (not reproduced) → action_observed; a seen decisive fact → state_seen; inferred-only vision →
    inferred_only; nothing valid → ungrounded. An unsafe/unverified transition can NEVER be replay-backed.

Deterministic validation proves STRUCTURE + PROVENANCE, not semantic meaning — fact ids alone never prove
entailment (that is the critic's job). Backward-compatible: no groundingV1 → no-op (existing tests green).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
