MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Makes ARCHITECT_SYSTEM_V2 REACHABLE through the real mission-generation entrypoint (runMissionBrain,
which inspectAndPlan calls), behind MISSION_GROUNDING_MODE=off|shadow|enforce (default off; unknown→off;
enforce implemented but NOT enabled).

  - mission-grounding-shadow.ts: ARCHITECT_SYSTEM_V2 (grounded, strict structured output) + CRITIC_SYSTEM_V2
    (per-criterion supported/partially/unsupported/contradictory, reject-or-downgrade only).
    runGroundedShadow() calls the V2 architect (fail-closed parse — a malformed response yields NO
    candidates, never a repaired plan), runs the digest-bound + replay-aware deterministic grounding
    validation, runs the grounding-aware critic (fail-closed → not supported), classifies each criterion's
    tier, and returns a bounded GroundingShadowResult (counts, enums, tier distribution, coverage,
    unsafe-transition count, disagreement vs the legacy accepted count) — no raw corpus. The architect
    model is unchanged (missionModel = the configured flash-lite).
  - runMissionBrain runs the shadow AFTER the legacy plan when the mode is not off, best-effort (fully
    caught): the legacy `accepted` selection and budget are NEVER changed; the result carries an advisory
    groundingShadow field. Off mode makes NO V2 call.
  - mission-metrics: promotionClean is now false whenever there are zero accepted candidates, zero
    grounded candidates, or an accepted criterion is unmapped.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
