Entrypoint integration tests: the REAL runMissionBrain (the function inspectAndPlan calls) runs for real —
its legacy architect, critic, deterministic gate, AND runGroundedShadow — with only the external LLM
provider boundary (llmCompleteJson) faked by scripted JSON keyed on the system prompt.

  A  SHADOW runs the V2 architect, the digest-bound deterministic grounding validation, and the critic;
     a grounded mission is structurally valid + critic-supported + accepted (state_seen tier).
  D  a ghost-feature mission (cites a non-existent fact) → structurally invalid, not accepted.
  G  a wrong observationSetDigest → rejected deterministically.
  L  SHADOW ISOLATION: with the V2 architect throwing, the legacy accepted count + reason are UNCHANGED
     and the job never fails (the throw is caught inside runGroundedShadow).
  M  OFF mode makes ZERO V2 architect calls and attaches no shadow.
  +  empty V2 output is recorded honestly as v2_empty.

Also breaks the mission-brain ↔ mission-grounding-shadow require cycle with a dynamic import at the call
site (a static CJS import captured the binding as undefined at load time).

No CommonStack calls (all provider responses are scripted fakes) — this is plumbing + gate evaluation,
not live model-quality evidence.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
